@node "Introduction" "About QWKGate"
@{b}-- Introduction --@{ub}


@{b}@{u}QWKGate :@{ub}@{uu}

QWKGate is a program to convert QWK-mail packets into Fido-mail packets so
you can use these in Fido-mail programs such as Spot, April, PM, ect.

If you haven't installed one of these programs (Spot, April, etc.) yet, you
must first install these before you continue.

After you have read your messages and answeres and made new messages you can
convert them back to a QWK reply packet. This packet can be transported
(uploaded) to the BBS.

The idea for writing QWKGate became when I began to mail at the Amiga
Magazine BBS with a QWK reader/writer. About the same time I became a point
of Grafix Attack BBS, which works with Fido-mail. I noticed that the
Fido-mail programs had much more options for saving and manufactoring of
messages. QWK-mail programs didn't have these options. You can only save or
delete the entire QWK packet. When I found a Arexx script on a BBS which
made it possible to convert a QWK-mail packet into a Fido-mail packet, the
idea for writing  QWKGate was born. After intensive programming and
beta-testing, this is QWKGate; have lots of fun!

@{b}@{u}QWKGate_Prefs :@{ub}@{uu}

QWKGate_Prefs is a utilitie for making/editing of '.BBS'-config-files for
QWKGate.

With the help of het default-settings even the beginner can simply make a
working config-file and edit it to its own preferences. The more experienced
user can simply make controle and edit it. 


QWKGate_Prefs proceeded when Beta-testing QWKGate. While expanding/updating
QWKGate there proceeded (too) many options. At that moment I got the idea
for making a Prefs-Editor for QWKGate, for automaticly processing the
converting from QWK to Fido and back.

This editor is made in coorporation with the programmer of QWKGate, Richard
de Vos. Therefore my credits.
@endnode

