@node "Use" "Use"
@{b}-- Use --@{ub}


@{b}@{u}QWKGate_Prefs :@{ub}@{uu}


@{b}The making of a config:@{ub}

You can use QWKGate_Prefs as any other Pref-editor.

See for the explanation of the commands @{"Configuration" alink "Configuration" 0}.


@{b}Automaticly loading of a .BBS-file at startup:@{ub}

For automaticly loading of a .BBS-file you must do the following:

- Press once on the QWKGate_Pref icon.

- Select Information from the Workbench-menu.

- As first Tool-Type you can give the path and the name of the '.BBS-file'.

  for example.  MAIL:DIVO.BBS

- Press RETURN and then 'Save'

The next time you startup QWKGate_Prefs the values of DIVO.BBS will be set
automaticly.



@{b}Saving a config-file:@{ub}

Select 'Save as...' in the menu, or press the 'Save'-gadget. A
file-requester will apear. Select the directory where the config-file must
be placed. Give a name, usualy the same name as the 'BBSID', for example
DIVO. The .BBS addition is not necessary, this will be automaticly
configured. The press 'OK'. The '.BBS-config-file' will be saved.
@endnode

